'''Android x86''' is an [[Android (operating system)|Android]] port to the [[Intel]] [[x86]] [[microprocessor]] family. The project was originally a set of patches to the Android source code but has now become separate. Its main goal was to have complete support on the [[ASUS Eee PC]], then to work on compatibility with other netbooks and [[UMPC]]s. The current project maintainers are [[Chih-Wei Huang]] and Yi Sun. {{As of|November 2011}}, its latest release is 2.3.7.
